On 07May2011 00:41, MRAB <python@mrabarnett.plus.com> wrote:
| As far as I remember, Ada also permits it,

That's where I first encountered it myself.

| but has the rule that it can
| occur only between digits. If we follow that, then:
| 
|     1_2345_6789 => Yes
|     1_2_3_4_5 => Yes
|     1_234_6789 => Yes
|     1_ => No
|     _1 => No
|     1__234 => No
|     9.876_543_210 => Yes
|     9._876_543_210 => No
|     9_.876_543_210 => No
|     0xFEFF_0042 => Yes
|     int('123_456') => Yes

+1 to this.

